<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>Last Updated: 11/4/2024</p>

<p>Thank you for using Study Group Finder! This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and share your information when you use our website and services. By accessing or using the Study Group Finder platform, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

<h3>a. Personal Information</h3>
<p>We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide when you:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Register an account</li>
    <li>Create or update your profile</li>
    <li>Use our messaging and communication features</li>
    <li>Participate in surveys or feedback requests</li>
</ul>
<p>This may include:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Name</li>
    <li>Email address</li>
    <li>School/University affiliation</li>
    <li>Study subjects and interests</li>
    <li>Preferred study times</li>
    <li>Profile picture (optional)</li>
</ul>

<h3>b. Usage Data</h3>
<p>We collect data on how you interact with our platform, which includes:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Login and logout times</li>
    <li>Pages visited</li>
    <li>Messages sent within the platform</li>
    <li>Preferences and settings</li>
</ul>

<h3>c. Device and Log Data</h3>
<p>To improve our services and ensure functionality, we collect device and log data, which may include:</p>
<ul>
    <li>IP address</li>
    <li>Browser type</li>
    <li>Device information</li>
    <li>Time and date of access</li>
    <li>Cookies (see Section 6)</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>The information we collect is used to:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Connect You with Study Partners:</strong> Use your preferences, interests, and availability to suggest suitable study partners or groups.</li>
    <li><strong>Improve Our Platform:</strong> Enhance our services, diagnose technical issues, and gather feedback.</li>
    <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Facilitate communication between you and other users on the platform.</li>
    <li><strong>Security:</strong> Monitor for and prevent potential fraud, unauthorized access, or any other misuse of our platform.</li>
</ul>
<p>We may use aggregated data (data that is anonymized and cannot identify you) for analytical purposes and to enhance our platform’s functionality.</p>

<h2>3. Sharing of Information</h2>
<p>Your privacy is important to us, and we only share your information in the following ways:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>With Other Users:</strong> To help you connect with study partners, limited information (such as your name, subjects of interest, and availability) is shared with other users in your network.</li>
    <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We may engage third-party providers to help us operate and maintain the platform (e.g., hosting services, data analytics). These providers only have access to your information to perform these tasks on our behalf and are obligated to protect it.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> We may disclose your information to comply with legal obligations, such as responding to a valid court order or regulatory request.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Your Choices</h2>
<p>You have control over your information and can make changes as needed:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Profile Settings:</strong> You may update or delete your profile information at any time through your account settings.</li>
    <li><strong>Communication Preferences:</strong> Opt out of non-essential communications (e.g., newsletters) through account settings or unsubscribe links in emails.</li>
    <li><strong>Account Deletion:</strong> You may request to delete your account at any time by contacting our support team. Note that some data may be retained for legal or security reasons.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Security of Your Information</h2>
<p>We use industry-standard measures to protect your information, including encryption, secure servers, and access controls. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

<h2>6. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
<p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to improve user experience, understand user interactions, and remember your preferences. You may modify your browser settings to disable cookies, though this may impact your ability to use certain features of the platform.</p>

<h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>Our platform is intended for users over the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from children under 13. If we become aware of data collected from a child under 13 without verified parental consent, we will take steps to delete it.</p>

<h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes to our practices, technology, or regulatory requirements. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. Please review this Privacy Policy from time to time.</p>

<h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:</p>
<p><strong>Study Group Finder Support</strong><br>
    Email: support@studygroupfinder.com<br>
    Address: UIA</p>

